article.headline: East Tenn. St. 110, Kennesaw 74
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Tim Smith had a triple-double and joined Courtney Pigram with 21 points each to help East Tennessee State pull away late in the first half for a 110-74 victory over Kennesaw on Wednesday night. ETSU (11-7, 8-3 Atlantic Sun) shot 58.4 percent, including 60.5 percent in the first half. The Buccaneers scored the last 10 points of the first half to lead 52-34 at halftime. Kennesaw (11-9, 9-2) trailed by double figures throughout the second half, getting only as close as 15 at 62-47 with 14:03 left. Smith had 10 assists and 10 rebounds, both team highs. Pigram had career highs with his 21 points, seven free throws, five rebounds and four steals. Dillion Sneed scored 17 for East Tennessee, Andrew Reed had 16 for 8-of-8 shooting and Travis Strong had 10. Golden Ingle led Kennesaw with 24 points, Ronnell Wooten had 15 and Brent Ragsdale 10. East Tennessee controlled the boards 45-25. Kennesaw shot 38.6 percent for the game.
